  "claim_short": "Let \\(u=P[h]\\) be the Poisson extension of \\(h\\in L^2(\\mathbb T,dt/(2\\pi))\\). If \\[ d\\mu(z)=(1-|z|^2)^{-2}\\,dA(z),\\qquad \\mu(\\Omega)=s<\\infty, \\] then \\[ \\int_\\Omega |u(z)|^2(1-|z|^2)^{-1}\\,dA(z) \\le 2\\pi\\log\\!\\left(1+\\frac{s}{\\pi}\\right)\\|h\\|_2^2. \\] The factor \\(2\\) is the best factor that works uniformly for all \\(s>0\\). The analytic sharp factor \\(1\\) fails for every fixed \\(s>0\\).",
